headline: Tapestry (TPR) Stock Trades Down, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of luxury fashion conglomerate Tapestry (NYSE:TPR) fell 1.9% in the afternoon session after Guggenheim initiated coverage on the company with a "Neutral" rating. The new coverage was led by analyst Simeon Siegel, who did not assign a price target as part of the initiation.
